text:
South Street, west side, south from, but not including Gouverneur Lane to Old Slip, showing across the barge at the rivers edge, the cleared area, upon which, the U.S. Assay Office building, will rise. Shown on the right, are Nos. 46 and 47 South Street; two 4-story buildings, just south of Gouverneur Lane. The white structure (left center), is the 1st Precinct Police Station.

December 13, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.
